==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Peakish
<hw>Peak"ish</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or relating to a
peak; or to peaks; belonging to a mountainous region.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Her
<xex>peakish</xex> spring.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Drayton.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧His
<xex>peakish</xex> dialect.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Bp. Hall.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having peaks; peaked.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Having features thin or sharp, as from sickness;
hence, sickly.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Peaky</ent>⟦br⟧
